Cell[TextData[{
 "Young's seminormal representation is not orthogonal with respect to the \
canonical Hermitian product. However, it is orthogonal with respect to a \
scalar product associated with a diagonal matrix, which may be regarded as \
the norm squares of basis vectors. A genuine orthogonal representation (i.e., \
Young's normal representation) can be achieved by simply dividing out the \
square roots of the diagonal elements, but then the resulting representation \
is no longer rational. See also ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["G\[UDoubleDot]nther (2019)"]], 
    "https://community.wolfram.com/groups/-/m/t/1637345"},
   "WebLink",
   BaseStyle->{"Notes"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "afdd158e-db90-4826-8b5e-294775f8b39a"],
 "."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->1644246267,ExpressionUUID->"6ba8e10d-5886-4de0-8818-8801a07e3bfb"]
}, Dynamic[CurrentValue[
 EvaluationNotebook[], {TaggingRules, "Openers", "NotesSection"}, Closed]]]],

